properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 8 at 10:36PM CST until January 9 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...WINTRY MIX OF PRECIPITATION EXPECTED THURSDAY...

.Low pressure approaching from the Northern Plains will produce a
mixture of snow, freezing drizzle and drizzle across northern and
central Wisconsin Thursday. While snow and ice accumulations are
expected to be relatively light, driving conditions will likely
become hazardous in some areas.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations
of up to one inch and ice accumulations up to one-tenth of an
inch.

* WHERE...Portions of north central and northeast Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From 8 AM to 9 PM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions by midday. The
hazardous conditions could impact the evening commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 8 AM TO 9 PM CST THURSDAY
